text: E tū is a New Zealand trade union created in October 2015 through the merger of the Service & Food Workers Union, the Flight Attendants and Related Services Union, and the Engineering, Printing and Manufacturing Union. It represents more than 50,000 workers. == References == Category:Trade unions in New Zealand Category:New Zealand Council of Trade Unions Category:Manufacturing trade unions Category:Trade unions established in 2015
title: E tū
